title: THE TRUE LIVES OF THE FABULOUS KILLJOYS 005 (2013) (digital) (So
description:
The True Lives of the Fabulous Killjoys is a 2013 comic book series written by Gerard Way and Shaun Simon with art by Becky Cloonan. The series serves as a sequel to the My Chemical Romance album Danger Days, focusing on the followers of the original Killjoys as they try to fight against the tyrannical mega-corporation Better Living Industries.

---

Fabulous Killjoys #5

"To put it as clearly as possible... there is something wrong with you and we are going to fix it."

Better Living Industries works to reeducate Korse and is met with deadly consequences just as the Girl learns lessons from her forgotten past. The big battle is brewing in the sands of the desert as the Killjoys march on Battery City!

From Gerard Way, creator of The Umbrella Academy!

One of Wired magazine's and IGN's Most Anticipated Comics of 2013!

"Buy into the hype. Killjoys... is killin' it." --Newsarama

Writers: Gerard Way, Shaun Simon
Artist: Becky Cloonan
Colorist: Dan Jackson

Genres: Science-Fiction, Action/Adventure

Publication Date: October 30, 2013
Full Color, 32 pages, Miniseries

Age range: 8 and up
